Review: Frustrating Account Requirement Ruins the Experience

I was excited to dive into this game, but I’ve been completely unable to play it due to an unnecessary and poorly implemented account creation requirement. Forcing players to make an account to access a game—when countless other titles offer seamless, account-free experiences—is baffling and feels like a thinly veiled attempt to track user data.

Worse, the account creation process is broken. After three days, I’m still stuck because the verification email never arrives in my inbox, likely due to some issue with their proxy servers or email system. I’ve paid for a game I can’t even play, hitting a brick wall of frustration before the game even starts. This is unacceptable, especially when the account system adds no value to the player experience. It appears to be a common issue with them as it is among the top issues in FAQ section about not receiving verification emails.  I have done all the things suggested in the troubleshooting for this issue, yet it still persists. The fact that I would even have to:  

Clear browser cache/cookies;
- Allow Pop-ups and Redirects in your browser settings;
- Temporarily disable extensions like Adblock;
- If you're using a mobile device, please try to access the website from a PC/Laptop;
- Try a different browser.
- Alternatively, if the issue persists, we would also highly recommend trying again at a later time.

...just to create an unnecessary "ACCOUNT" to play the game is 7+ steps too far just to play the game.

Until they fix this intrusive and dysfunctional account requirement, I can’t recommend this game. Save your money and play one of the thousands of other titles that respect your time and privacy.

Rating: 1/5

Things rockstar could do to further improve the "Definitive edition" game:

- Let us switch from original graphics to remastered graphics (Just like in Halo MCC) ;
- Restore all the original music tracks that were previously removed or at the very least add new ones ;
- Restore the target npc health indicator when playing on mouse and keyboard ;
- Make fog more noticeable, especially on foggy weather! ;
- Make the LS police uniform black just like in the original ;
- Some character models need a touch up ;

Most people who grew up playing the original (like me) will have tons of fun, however the team that made this "Remaster" had no love or respect to the original game.

The game is in a much better state now than when it was released, but they should keep releasing updates until it is worth the money they ask !
If you really want to play it, wait for sales.

